ddf.catalog.data.metacardtype

Class MetacardTypeRegistryImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • ddf.catalog.data.metacardtype.MetacardTypeRegistryImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MetacardTypeRegistry

    public final class MetacardTypeRegistryImpl
extends Object
implements MetacardTypeRegistry
    Default implementation of the MetacardTypeRegistry.

    This code is experimental. While this class is functional and tested, it may change or be removed in a future version of the library.

      • register

        public void register(QualifiedMetacardType qualifiedMetacardType)
              throws IllegalArgumentException
        Description copied from interface: MetacardTypeRegistry
        Registers a QualifiedMetacardType in the system so that it is accessible to InputTransformers, MetacardTransformers, QueryResponseTransformers, and other components. This allows those components to know how to properly interpret a Metacard and its Attributes. If the QualifiedMetacardType does not contain a namespace, the default namespace will be assumed.
        Specified by:
        register in interface MetacardTypeRegistry
        Parameters:
        qualifiedMetacardType - the QualifiedMetacardType to make available to the catalog framework.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - An IllegalArgumentException will be thrown if qualifiedMetacardType is null. An IllegalArgumentException will also be thrown if the QualifiedMetacardType 's name is null or empty.

        Specified by:

        metacardTypeName - unique name identifying MetacardType. Cannot be null or empty.
